@startuml use-cases-reporting
title trawhile — Reporting & Export (Epic 4)

left to right direction

actor "User" as User

rectangle "Reporting & Export" {
    usecase "View time report\n(filter by date, user, node)\n(UR-F036)" as UC_Report
    usecase "Toggle summary / detailed /\nchart view\n(UR-F037)" as UC_ReportMode
    usecase "Export report to CSV\n(UR-F038)" as UC_ExportCsv
    usecase "View member time summaries\n(per-bucket data quality flag)\n(UR-F052)" as UC_MemberSummaries
    usecase "View charts\n(time per node, time over period,\nper-member breakdown)\n(UR-F063)" as UC_Charts
    usecase "Export current view to PDF\n(UR-F064)" as UC_ExportPdf
    usecase "Report filter auto-saved\nand restored across sessions\n(UR-F066)" as UC_FilterPersist
}

User --> UC_Report
User --> UC_ReportMode
User --> UC_ExportCsv
User --> UC_MemberSummaries
User --> UC_Charts
User --> UC_ExportPdf

UC_Charts ..> UC_Report : <<extends>>
UC_ExportPdf ..> UC_ReportMode : <<extends>>
UC_FilterPersist ..> UC_Report : <<extends>>

note bottom of UC_FilterPersist
  Persisted automatically; no
  explicit user action required.
end note

@enduml
